<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="593" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1554,1579]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[804,900,1555,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Bagdadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricornis">
<emphasis box="[804,900,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">tricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning triangular, referring to the process of valva.
</paragraph>
